President Donald J. Trump, Vice President Mike Pence, and Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos recently met with students, teachers, and community leaders to discuss improving safety in schools across the country. The goal of the meeting was to gain perspective from individuals who have experienced acts of violence in schools. The participants discussed various topics including the need to reduce violence, improve access to resources, and focus on prevention. Many emphasized the importance of moving past partisan politics and finding common ground to work towards a solution. President Trump has expressed support for efforts to improve the federal background check system and ensure the safety of American children.